				<div class="post clearfix">
					<h1 class="title">Sweet &#038; Spicy Bacon Coated with Nutella</h1>
											<p class="post-meta">Posted  by <a href="http://www.bellalimento.com/author/paula/" title="Posts by Paula">Paula</a> in <a href="http://www.bellalimento.com/category/recipes/" title="View all posts in All Recipes" rel="category tag">All Recipes</a>, <a href="http://www.bellalimento.com/category/nutella/" title="View all posts in Nutella" rel="category tag">Nutella</a>, <a href="http://www.bellalimento.com/category/pork/" title="View all posts in Pork" rel="category tag">Pork</a> | <a href="http://www.bellalimento.com/2011/02/05/sweet-spicy-bacon-coated-with-nutella/#comments" title="Comment on Sweet &amp; Spicy Bacon Coated with Nutella">55 comments</a></p>
																				
								
					<p><span class="rdetector_placeholder_before"></span></p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-8273" title="nutellabacon6_wm" src="http://www.bellalimento.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/nutellabacon6_wm.jpg" alt="" width="570" height="400" /></p>
<p>It&#8217;s that time again, one of my favorite days of the year, <a href="http://www.nutelladay.com" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','outbound-article','www.nutelladay.com']);" target="_blank">WORLD NUTELLA DAY</a>! WND is the brainchild of <a href="http://msadventuresinitaly.com/blog" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','outbound-article','msadventuresinitaly.com']);" target="_blank">Sara</a> &amp; <a href="http://bleedingespresso.com/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','outbound-article','bleedingespresso.com']);" target="_blank">Michelle </a>who ask Nutella lovers to unite every February 5 creating a world blanket of Nutella love. How awesome it that ; ) To celebrate I&#8217;ve created a doozy of a Nutella recipe. Yes, I did. I covered bacon in Nutella. And guess what? It&#8217;s off the charts AMAZING. I know it might be a stretch for some, but if you take that leap of faith and try it, you just might find you like it. I&#8217;ll even go as far as say that you&#8217;ll LURVE it.<span id="more-8205"></span></p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-8268" title="nutellabacon1_wm" src="http://www.bellalimento.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/nutellabacon1_wm.jpg" alt="" width="570" height="750" /></p>
<p>It starts with a sweet and spicy bacon. It&#8217;s the only way I eat bacon anymore, I love it. I was at this quaint Bed &amp; Breakfast and they served this thick baked bacon with a sweet heat and I was hooked. I modified it a bit to fit my level of sweet heat and changed up the heat portion. It&#8217;s the perfect balance of flavors.</p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-8269" title="nutellabacon2_wm" src="http://www.bellalimento.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/nutellabacon2_wm.jpg" alt="" width="570" height="750" /></p>
<p>You have to start with a nice THICK sliced bacon. Then you&#8217;ll mix up your spice mixture {be careful not to touch your face or heaven forbid your eyes after this, trust me it&#8217;s brutal. You&#8217;re going to bake it for a bit, flip them and then sprinkle the mixture on and cook a wee bit longer. Now I know at this point you&#8217;ll want to eat the bacon, so go ahead and make a few extra pieces for &#8220;research&#8221; purposes. You&#8217;ll need to let them cool completely {a baking rack does a smashing job}</p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-8270" title="nutellabacon3_wm" src="http://www.bellalimento.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/nutellabacon3_wm.jpg" alt="" width="570" height="400" /></p>
<p>Then comes the magic. The NUTELLA magic. Just pop it into the microwave for a few seconds to soften it. You&#8217;ll need a easy touch here. If you get carried away and heavy handed you&#8217;ll risk cracking the bacon {&amp; hey worse case scenario you have smaller pieces to it} Now if you have a silicon brush that would be ideal, or even an icing spatula to spread the Nutella over the bacon.</p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-8272" title="nutellabacon5_wm" src="http://www.bellalimento.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/nutellabacon5_wm.jpg" alt="" width="570" height="750" /></p>
<p>Now you could at this point eat it, but it will be VERY messy, so just  be patient a little longer. Pop them into the fridge or even freezer if you just can&#8217;t stand it until the Nutella hardens and creates a beautiful coating.</p>
<p>And then the final touch a sprinkling of fleur de sel&#8230; Oh my goodness, it&#8217;s a sweet, spicy and salty sinfully scrumptious SNACK!</p>
<p>I<strong>f you LOVE Nutella, you&#8217;ll love our newly launched Nutella eye-candy site: <a href="http://www.bellanutella.com" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','outbound-article','www.bellanutella.com']);" target="_blank">BELLA NUTELLA</a>&#8230; Prepararti ; ) Prepare yourselves&#8230; It&#8217;s ALL Nutella, ALL the time! </strong></p>
<p>Baci!</p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-6221" title="signature2010" src="http://www.bellalimento.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/signature2010.png" alt="" width="250" height="80" /></p>
<p><br />
<a href="http://www.bellalimento.com/2011/02/05/sweet-spicy-bacon-coated-with-nutella/print/"  title="Print This Recipe" rel="nofollow"><img class="WP-PrintIcon" src="http://www.bellalimento.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-print/images/print.gif" alt="Print This Recipe" title="Print This Recipe" style="border: 0px;" /></a></p>
<p><em>Sweet &amp; Spicy Bacon coated with Nutella and garnished with fleur del sel</em><br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline;">What you&#8217;ll need:</span><br />
1 tablespoon light brown sugar<br />
1 teaspoon chili powder<br />
1 teaspoon black pepper<br />
6 pieces &#8211; thick sliced bacon<br />
3 tablespoons Nutella<br />
fleur de sel</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">What to do:</span><br />
1.Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Into a small bowl mix: sugar, chili powder and black pepper. Set aside.</p>
<p>2. Spray a rimmed baking sheet with cooking spray. Arrange bacon sliced onto baking sheet making sure slices do not overlap. Bake for approximately 8 minutes. CAREFULLY flip bacon slices and sprinkle sugar/pepper mixture onto slices. Return to oven and bake for an additional 8 minutes.</p>
<p>3. Transfer bacon slices to a cooling rack and allow to cool completely.</p>
<p>4. When bacon has cooled, place Nutella into a small bowl and microwave for approximately 15-20 seconds to allow to soften. Transfer bacon slices to a piece of parchment paper that sits a top a plate. Using a silicon brush or icing spatula gently spread Nutella onto each bacon slice. Place plate into refrigerator and allow Nutella to coat/harden.</p>
<p>5. Once coating is firm to the touch sprinkle with fleur de sel.</p>
<p>Buon Appetito!
<p><a id="magellan"></a><br />
